00:15:28.450 --> 00:15:33.760
So Victor Martinez was a
really good friend of mine,

00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:36.910
a meticulous poet and writer.

00:15:36.910 --> 00:15:43.050
And he got the National Book Award
for Parrot in the Oven in 1996.

00:15:43.050 --> 00:15:46.870
And he got it by just cracking
each line into little pieces

00:15:46.870 --> 00:15:52.060
and just really worked so hard
on the language and the story

00:15:52.060 --> 00:15:54.060
and everything you
could ever imagine.

00:15:54.060 --> 00:15:58.490
Every word in that book is
measured and weighted and looked

00:15:58.490 --> 00:16:03.550
at from a thousand angles, from
20 feet away, pinned on the wall,

00:16:03.550 --> 00:16:07.010
and then he would literally use it.

00:16:07.010 --> 00:16:11.800
He passed away in 2011
from lung cancer.

00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:13.730
A lot of my good friends
have passed away

00:16:13.730 --> 00:16:19.010
from cancer recently,
the last ten, 15 years.

00:16:19.010 --> 00:16:23.700
And I had written him some poems
early on called Undelivered Letters

00:16:23.700 --> 00:16:26.760
to Victor while he was alive.

00:16:26.760 --> 00:16:30.910
So I remember him saying --

00:16:30.910 --> 00:16:33.890
he was really a deep guy,
a really deep thinker.

00:16:33.890 --> 00:16:37.860
And on the back of his only
poetry collection called Caring

00:16:37.860 --> 00:16:40.630
for a House, he says quite a bit.

00:16:40.630 --> 00:16:43.180
He writes a big old, giant
paragraph on the back of that book,

00:16:43.180 --> 00:16:46.980
and he talks about this thing
he calls super imagination.

00:16:46.980 --> 00:16:51.700 position:56%
And who knows, you know, if it's
Quantum Theory or super imagination,

00:16:51.700 --> 00:16:56.390
and all about being in two
places at the same time.

00:16:57.490 --> 00:17:00.350
So I always think of him.

00:17:00.350 --> 00:17:06.490
So this is called Thought Poem
for Victor Martinez, Undelivered.

00:17:06.490 --> 00:17:12.380
Still thinking about super time,
super space and super imagination.

00:17:12.380 --> 00:17:16.620
You said what you wrote
was being written

00:17:16.620 --> 00:17:21.740
by someone somewhere
else at the same time.

00:17:21.740 --> 00:17:28.890
Some country, some town, in a
broken bus or a polished grain desk

00:17:28.890 --> 00:17:33.890
or a cheap clinic deep in
the rainforest somehow.

00:17:33.890 --> 00:17:38.330
A hut fixed with branches
and strings.

00:17:38.330 --> 00:17:42.310
Just maybe a school tilted en route

00:17:42.310 --> 00:17:45.790
to tumbo-by-baneke
[phonetic] somewhere.

00:17:45.790 --> 00:17:48.480
What would you be writing?

00:17:48.480 --> 00:17:52.390
It does not matter and why.

00:17:52.390 --> 00:17:54.850
Poetry -- why that?

00:17:54.850 --> 00:17:59.870
Why continue its tiny
mouth on a page?

00:17:59.870 --> 00:18:01.170
Why not a simple message,

00:18:01.170 --> 00:18:08.790
just a message there is more
hunger than poetry, Vic.

00:18:08.790 --> 00:18:12.730 position:56%
I am pushing down the 300 buildings.

00:18:12.730 --> 00:18:18.210
There is thirst, Vic, more
thirst than knowledge.

00:18:18.210 --> 00:18:23.690
You always spoke of this thing,
knowledge, you read Heidegger.

00:18:23.690 --> 00:18:26.910
What is thinking more
than knowledge?

00:18:26.910 --> 00:18:31.090
Vic, how about knowledge
in the hand?

00:18:31.090 --> 00:18:33.420
In the gut?

00:18:33.420 --> 00:18:36.290
Water from a storm.

00:18:36.290 --> 00:18:42.250
Hunger in the center of your
flesh; not flesh, is not knowledge.

00:18:42.250 --> 00:18:44.790
It is pure insight, sinew.

00:18:44.790 --> 00:18:46.820
It is edge.

00:18:46.820 --> 00:18:52.460
More edge than poem paper
poems are not bread.

00:18:52.460 --> 00:18:54.620
I am calling for bread.

00:18:54.620 --> 00:18:57.080
With empty offices at night,

00:18:57.080 --> 00:19:03.940 position:56%
the ones across from my tenth floor
poetry bed door, D.C. Somewhere else

00:19:03.940 --> 00:19:11.850 position:56%
in the variety realms, even though
I am here, brother, and you are not.

00:19:11.850 --> 00:19:15.140
So that's the Thought
Poem for Victor Martinez

00:19:15.140 --> 00:19:19.620
that I hammered out this morning.

